 sections , div,.. block elements are used to seperate the pages in logical order
  such as top-part, pricing, comments, adds,...

  ---containers-------
  container : gives some spacing in the right and left
  container-fluid : making the full width

  ---background collors---
  bg-primary
  bg-secondary
  bg-warning
  ......
  -----text colors----
.text-primary
.text-secondary
.text-success
.text-danger
.text-warning
.text-info
.text-light
.text-dark
  ....

  -----nav-bar----
  we can create nav really quick
  navbar-dark  : use when background is dark to make text light
  navbar-light : use when background is light to make text dark

  ---grid system------
col-lg-3  : 3 units on a large screen - meading 3/12 part of the entire screen
col-md-6  : 6 units on a medium screen - meading 6/12 part of the entire screen
col-sm-12 : 12 units on a small screen - meading 12/12 part of the entire screen
        <div class="row">
          <div class="col-lg-3 col-md-6 col-sm-12">
           Col 1
          </div>
          <div class="col-lg-3 col-md-6 col-sm-12">
          Col 2
          </div>
          <div class="col-lg-3 col-md-6 col-sm-12">
           Col3
          </div>
        </div>
-------spacing--------
Where property is one of:

m - for classes that set margin
p - for classes that set padding
Where sides is one of:

t - for classes that set margin-top or padding-top
b - for classes that set margin-bottom or padding-bottom
l - for classes that set margin-left or padding-left
r - for classes that set margin-right or padding-right
x - for classes that set both *-left and *-right
y - for classes that set both *-top and *-bottom
blank - for classes that set a margin or padding on all 4 sides of the element
Where size is one of:

0 - for classes that eliminate the margin or padding by setting it to 0
1 - (by default) for classes that set the margin or padding to $spacer * .25
2 - (by default) for classes that set the margin or padding to $spacer * .5
3 - (by default) for classes that set the margin or padding to $spacer
4 - (by default) for classes that set the margin or padding to $spacer * 1.5
5 - (by default) for classes that set the margin or padding to $spacer * 3
auto - for classes that set the margin to auto
(You can add more sizes by adding entries to the $spacers Sass map variable.)

EXAMPLE: mt-3 : margin top 3
         pt-5 : padding top 5
         m-2  : margin all around


